snippet: A Polish military prosecutor shot himself in the head on Monday after cutting short a news conference, although his life was not in danger.
abstract: Polish military prosecutor Mikolaj Przybyl shoots himself in the head after cutting short a news conference; apparent suicide attempt sets off public dispute between the heads of Poland's military and civilian prosecution services over merger plans, which Przybyl had criticized.
lead_paragraph: A Polish military prosecutor shot himself in the head on Monday after cutting short a news conference, although his life was not in danger.

headline.main: Poland: Prosecutor Shoots Himself Amid Turf War Between Agencies
headline.print_headline: Poland: Prosecutor Shoots Self Amid Turf War Between Agencies
